241A 101st Legislative Session 241
2026 South Dakota Legislature
Senate Bill 241
AMENDME NT 241A
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Senator Grove
1 An Act to require that the Department of Revenue provide an annual report to Indian
2 tribes tribal governments regarding certain tax collections.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 10-12A:
5 Prior to December first of each year, the department shall provide a report to each
6 Indian tribe tribal government that has entered into a tax collection agreement under the
7 provisions of this chapter and chapter 1-24, estimating the amount of tax collected under
8 a tax collection agreement from January first through December thirty-first of the prior
9 year for each tax included in § 10-12A-4, within the area covered by the tax collection
10 agreement.
11 The annual report must distinguish between tax revenue collected from remote
12 sellers and nonremote sellers.
13 Prior to December 1, 2026, the department shall provide the report required by
14 this section for the years 2020, 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024, and 2025.
15 Section 2. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 10-12A:
16 Prior to December first of each year, the department shall provide a report to each
17 Indian tribe tribal government that has not entered into a tax collection agreement, and
18 to Indian tribes with citizens residing on tribal lands outside the tax collection agreement
19 areas under the provisions of this chapter and chapter 1-24, estimating, based on the
20 proportion of a county's population that consists of who are members of an Indian tribe
21 according to the latest federal census, the amount of tax collected under a tax collection
22 agreement from January first through December thirty-first of the prior year from tribal
23 members for each tax included in § 10-12A-4 within the boundaries of the following
24 counties:
25 (1) Bennett County;
